TOGEDEMARU.blurb: When it's surprised or agitated, the 14 fur spikes on its back will stand up involuntarily.
TOGEDEMARU.name: Togedemaru

MIMIKYU.blurb: It conceals its terrifying appearance beneath an old rag so it can get closer to people and Pokémon.
MIMIKYU.name: Mimikyu

BRUXISH.blurb: Its skin is thick enough to fend off spikes. With its robust teeth, it crunches up and eats the spikes.
BRUXISH.name: Bruxish

DRAMPA.blurb: It appears in towns and plays with the children. Drampa will protect kids when they're in danger.
DRAMPA.name: Drampa

DHELMISE.blurb: It wraps its prey in green seaweed and sucks away their vitality. It only likes to go after big prey.
DHELMISE.name: Dhelmise

JANGMO_O.blurb: They live in mountains where no trace of humans can be detected. It grows as it battles others.

HAKAMO_O.blurb: It leaps at its prey with a courageous shout. Its scaly punches tear its opponents to shreds.

KOMMO_O.blurb: It battles valiantly with its fists, which are armored in steel scales. Kommo-o specializes in uppercuts.

TAPU_KOKO.name: Tapu Koko

TAPU_LELE.name: Tapu Lele

TAPU_BULU.blurb: The guardian deity of Ula'ula is a lazy Pokémon. It commands plants to immobilize its foes.
TAPU_BULU.name: Tapu Bulu

TAPU_FINI.name: Tapu Fini

COSMOEM.blurb: As it absorbs light, Cosmoem continues to grow. Its golden shell is surprisingly solid.
COSMOEM.name: Cosmoem

SOLGALEO.blurb: In writings from the distant past, it's called by the name "the beast that devours the sun.\"

LUNALA.blurb: It sometimes summons unknown powers and life-forms to this world from holes that lead to other worlds.
LUNALA.name: Lunala

NIHILEGO.name: Nihilego

BUZZWOLE.name: Buzzwole

PHEROMOSA.blurb: One of the dangerous Ultra Beasts, it has been spotted running across the land at terrific speeds.
PHEROMOSA.name: Pheromosa

XURKITREE.blurb: It appeared from the Ultra Wormhole. It raided a power plant, so it energizes itself with electricity.
XURKITREE.name: Xurkitree

CELESTEELA.blurb: It appeared from the Ultra Wormhole. Witnesses observed it flying across the sky at high speed.
CELESTEELA.name: Celesteela

KARTANA.blurb: This Ultra Beast's body, which is as thin as paper, is like a sharpened sword.
KARTANA.name: Kartana

GUZZLORD.blurb: An unknown life-form called a UB. It may be constantly hungry-it is certainly always devouring something.
GUZZLORD.name: Guzzlord

NECROZMA.blurb: Light is the source of its energy. If it isn't devouring light, impurities build up in it.
NECROZMA.name: Necrozma

MAGEARNA.blurb: Its mechanized body is merely a vessel. Its true self is its Soul-Heart, an artificial soul.
MAGEARNA.name: Magearna

MARSHADOW.name: Marshadow

RATICATE_A.blurb: It makes its Rattata underlings gather food for it, dining solely on the most nutritious and delicious fare.

RAICHU_A.blurb: It focuses psychic energy into its tail and rides it like it's surfing. Another name for this Pokémon is "hodad.\"

VULPIX_A.blurb: In hot weather, this Pokémon makes ice shards with its six tails and sprays them around to cool itself off.

NINETALES_A.blurb: It lives on mountains perpetually covered in snow and is revered as a deity incarnate.

DIGLETT_A.blurb: Its golden hairs function as sensors. It pokes them out of its burrow to monitor its surroundings.

DUGTRIO_A.blurb: Its metallic whiskers are heavy, so it's not very fast, but it has the power to dig through bedrock.

MEOWTH_A.blurb: It's impulsive, selfish, and fickle. It's very popular with Trainers who like giving it the attention it needs.

PERSIAN_A.blurb: It has the classiest coat. The rippling of its fur in the heat of battle has a beauty all its own.

GEODUDE_A.blurb: Its body is a magnetic stone. Iron sand attaches firmly to the portions of its body that are particularly magnetic.

GOLEM_A.blurb: Since it can't fire boulders at a rapid pace, it's been known to seize nearby Geodude and fire them from its back.

MUK_A.blurb: The garbage it eats causes continuous chemical changes in its body, which produce its vivid coloration.

MAROWAK_A.blurb: Its custom is to mourn its lost friends. Mounds of dirt by the side of the road mark the graves of the Marowak.

ORICORIO_P.blurb: This Oricorio has sipped pink nectar. Its enemies' hearts melt at the sight of its gently swaying hips.

ORICORIO_S.blurb: This Oricorio has sipped purple nectar. Some dancers use its graceful, elegant dancing as inspiration.

LYCANROC_N.blurb: They live alone without forming packs. They only listen to orders from those who can draw out their true power.

WISHIWASHI_S.blurb: At their appearance, even Gyarados flee. When they team up to use Water Gun, its power exceeds that of Hydro Pump.

MAGEARNA_P.blurb: It functions thanks to its artificial soul. The vivid decoration is proof that it was presented as a gift to royalty.

POIPOLE.blurb: This Ultra Beast is well enough liked to be chosen as a first partner in its own world.
POIPOLE.name: Poipole

NAGANADEL.blurb: It stores hundreds of liters of poisonous liquid in its body. It is one of the organisms known as UBs.

STAKATAKA.blurb: When stone walls started moving and attacking, the brute's true identity was this mysterious life-form.
STAKATAKA.name: Stakataka

BLACEPHALON.blurb: It causes explosions, then takes advantage of opponents' surprise to rob them of their vitality.

ZERAORA.blurb: It approaches its enemies at the speed of lightning, then tears them limb from limb with its sharp claws.
ZERAORA.name: Zeraora

LYCANROC_DUSK.blurb: This strange form is the result of it evolving at dusk. An intense fighting spirit underlies its calmness.

MELTAN.blurb: It melts particles of iron and other metals found in the subsoil, so it can absorb them into its molten steel body.

MELMETAL.blurb: Revered long ago for its capacity to create iron from nothing, it has come back to life after 3000 years.
MELMETAL.name: Melmetal

GROOKEY.name: Grookey

THWACKEY.blurb: The faster a Thwackey can beat out a rhythm with its two sticks, the more respect it wins from its peers.
THWACKEY.name: Thwackey

RILLABOOM.name: Rillaboom

SCORBUNNY.blurb: It has special pads on the backs of its feet, and one on its nose. Its pads radiate tremendous heat.

RABOOT.blurb: Its thick and fluffy fur protects it from the cold and enables it to use hotter fire moves.
RABOOT.name: Raboot

CINDERACE.blurb: It gets pumped up when cheered on. But if it starts showboating, it could put itself in a tough spot.
CINDERACE.name: Cinderace

SOBBLE.blurb: When it gets wet, its skin changes color, and this Pokémon becomes invisible as if it were camouflaged.
SOBBLE.name: Sobble

DRIZZILE.blurb: Highly intelligent but also very lazy, it keeps enemies out of its territory by laying traps everywhere.
DRIZZILE.name: Drizzile

INTELEON.blurb: It picks out foes' weak points so it can precisely blast them with water that shoots from its fingertips.
INTELEON.name: Inteleon

SKWOVET.blurb: This Pokémon becomes uneasy if its cheeks are ever completely empty of berries.
SKWOVET.name: Skwovet

GREEDENT.blurb: This Pokémon has strong teeth and can chew through the toughest of berry shells.
GREEDENT.name: Greedent

ROOKIDEE.blurb: It will bravely challenge any foe, no matter how powerful. Even suffering a defeat increases its strength a bit.
ROOKIDEE.name: Rookidee

CORVISQUIRE.blurb: The lessons of many harsh battles have taught it how to accurately judge an opponent's strength.
CORVISQUIRE.name: Corvsquire

CORVIKNIGHT.blurb: The black luster of its steel body could drive terror into the heart of any foe.
CORVIKNIGHT.name: Corvknight

BLIPBUG.blurb: A constant collector of information, this Pokémon is very smart. Very strong is what it isn't.
BLIPBUG.name: Blipbug

DOTTLER.blurb: As it grows inside its shell, it uses its psychic abilities to monitor its surroundings and wait for evolution.
DOTTLER.name: Dottler

ORBEETLE.blurb: It's famous for its high intelligence, and the large size of its brain is proof that it has immense psychic power.
ORBEETLE.name: Orbeetle

NICKIT.blurb: Aided by the soft pads on its feet, it silently raids the food stores of others. It survives off its ill-gotten gains.
NICKIT.name: Nickit

THIEVUL.blurb: With a lithe body and sharp claws, it goes around stealing food and eggs. It secretly marks its future targets.
THIEVUL.name: Thievul

GOSSIFLEUR.blurb: It anchors itself in the ground and basks in the sun. After absorbing enough sunlight, it blooms vividly.
GOSSIFLEUR.name: Gossifleur

ELDEGOSS.blurb: The seeds attached to its cotton fluff are full of nutrients. It spreads them on the wind so that others can benefit.
ELDEGOSS.name: Eldegoss

WOOLOO.blurb: If its fleece grows too long, it won't be able to move. Cloth made with its wool is surprisingly durable.
WOOLOO.name: Wooloo

DUBWOOL.blurb: Its majestic horns are meant only to impress the opposite gender. They never see use in battle.
DUBWOOL.name: Dubwool

CHEWTLE.blurb: Apparently the itch of its teething impels it to snap its jaws at anything in front of it.
CHEWTLE.name: Chewtle

DREDNAW.blurb: With jaws that can shear through steel rods, this highly aggressive Pokémon chomps down on its unfortunate prey.
DREDNAW.name: Drednaw

YAMPER.blurb: This greedy Pokémon only helps people with their work because it wants treats. As it runs, it crackles with electricity.
YAMPER.name: Yamper

BOLTUND.blurb: It sends electricity through its legs to boost their strength. Running at top speed, it easily breaks 50 mph.
BOLTUND.name: Boltund

ROLYCOLY.blurb: It can race around like a unicycle, even on rough, rocky terrain. Burning coal sustains it.
ROLYCOLY.name: Rolycoly

CARKOL.blurb: By rapidly rolling its legs, it can easily travel at over 18 mph. It forms coal inside its body.
CARKOL.name: Carkol

COALOSSAL.blurb: While engaged in battle, its mountain of coal will burn bright red, scorching the surrounding area with sparks.
COALOSSAL.name: Coalossal

APPLIN.blurb: As soon as it's born, it burrows into an apple. the flavor of the apple is what determines its evolution.
APPLIN.name: Applin

FLAPPLE.blurb: It ate a sour apple, which induced its evolution. It stores an acid capable of causing chemical burns in its cheeks.
FLAPPLE.name: Flapple

APPLETUN.blurb: It ate a sweet apple, which induced its evolution. Back in the day, children used to have it as a snack.
APPLETUN.name: Appletun

SILICOBRA.blurb: It spews sand from its nostrils. While the enemy is blinded, it burrows into the ground to hide.
SILICOBRA.name: Silicobra

SANDACONDA.blurb: When it contracts its body, over 220 pounds of sand sprays from its nose. It becomes disheartened if it runs out.
SANDACONDA.name: Sandaconda

CRAMORANT.blurb: This hungry Pokémon swallows Arrokuda whole. Occasionally, it makes a mistake and tries to swallow other Pokémon.
CRAMORANT.name: Cramorant

ARROKUDA.blurb: It becomes extremely sluggish after eating its fill. That's when Cramorant swallows it up.
ARROKUDA.name: Arrokuda

BARRASKEWDA.blurb: Its jaw that's as sharp as a spear and as strong as steel. It spins its tail fins to surge forward at over 100 knots.
BARRASKEWDA.name: Baraskewda

TOXEL.blurb: It manipulates the chemical makeup of its poison to produce electricity. Despite a weak voltage, it can cause paralysis.
TOXEL.name: Toxel

TOXTRICITY.blurb: This short-tempered and aggressive Pokémon chugs stagnant water to absorb any toxins it might contain.
TOXTRICITY.name: Toxtricity

SIZZLIPEDE.blurb: It stores flammable gas in its body and uses it to generate heat. It then coils around its prey and cooks it.
SIZZLIPEDE.name: Sizzlipede

CENTISKORCH.blurb: This excessively hostile Pokémon has large and very sharp fangs in addition to its dangerous burning body.
CENTISKORCH.name: Centskorch

CLOBBOPUS.blurb: It's very curious, but its means of investigating things is to try to punch them with its tentacles.
CLOBBOPUS.name: Clobbopus

GRAPPLOCT.blurb: Searching for an opponent to test its skills against, it emerges onto land. Once the battle is over, it returns to the sea.
GRAPPLOCT.name: Grapploct

SINISTEA.blurb: This Pokémon is said to have been born when a lonely spirit possessed a cold, leftover cup of tea.
SINISTEA.name: Sinistea

POLTEAGEIST.blurb: This species lives in antique teapots. Most pots are forgeries, but on rare occasions, an authentic work is found.
POLTEAGEIST.name: Poltegeist

HATENNA.blurb: Via the protrusion on its head, it senses other creatures' emotions. It prefers areas without people.
HATENNA.name: Hatenna

HATTREM.blurb: No matter who you are, if you bring strong emotions near this Pokémon, it will silence you violently.
HATTREM.name: Hattrem

HATTERENE.blurb: Known as the Forest Witch, if you are too loud around it, you risk being torn apart by the claws on its tentacle.
HATTERENE.name: Hatterene

IMPIDIMP.blurb: It sneaks into people's homes, taking and feasting on the negative energy of the frustrated occupants.
IMPIDIMP.name: Impidimp

MORGREM.blurb: With sly cunning, it lures people into the woods. Some believe it to have the power to make crops grow.
MORGREM.name: Morgrem

GRIMMSNARL.blurb: Its hairs work like muscle fibers. When its hairs unfurl, they latch on to foes, ensnaring them like tentacles.
GRIMMSNARL.name: Grimmsnarl

OBSTAGOON.blurb: It evolved after experiencing numerous fights. While crossing its arms, it lets out a shout that'd make anyone flinch.
OBSTAGOON.name: Obstagoon

PERRSERKER.blurb: What appears to be an iron helmet is actually hardened hair. This Pokémon lives for the thrill of battle.
PERRSERKER.name: Perrserker

CURSOLA.blurb: Be cautious of the ectoplasmic body surrounding its soul. You'll become stiff as stone if you touch it.
CURSOLA.name: Cursola

SIRFETCHD.blurb: After deflecting attacks with its hard leaf shield, it strikes back with its sharp leek stalk.
SIRFETCHD.name: Sirfetch'd

MR_RIME.blurb: Its amusing movements make it very popular. It releases its psychic power from the pattern on its belly.
MR_RIME.name: Mr. Rime

RUNERIGUS.blurb: Never touch its shadowlike body, or you'll be shown the horrific memories behind the picture carved into it.
RUNERIGUS.name: Runerigus

MILCERY.blurb: They say that any patisserie visited by Milcery is guaranteed success and good fortune.
MILCERY.name: Milcery

ALCREMIE_STRAWBERRY.blurb: It evolved from a Milcery that held onto a Strawberry Sweet. Its flavor depends on how it was mixed.
ALCREMIE_STRAWBERRY.name: Alcremie

FALINKS.blurb: The six of them work together as one. Teamwork is also their battle strategy, and they constantly change formation.
FALINKS.name: Falinks

PINCURCHIN.blurb: It feeds on seaweed, using its teeth to scrape it off rocks. Electric current flows from the tips of its spines.
PINCURCHIN.name: Pincurchin

SNOM.blurb: It eats snow that piles up on the ground. The more snow it eats, the bigger its spikes grow.
SNOM.name: Snom

FROSMOTH.blurb: Icy scales fall from its wings like snow as it flies over fields and mountains.
FROSMOTH.name: Frosmoth

STONJOURNER.blurb: Once a year, on a specific date and at a specific time, they gather out of nowhere and form up in a circle.
STONJOURNER.name: Stonjorner

EISCUE.blurb: It drifted in on the flow of ocean waters from a frigid place. It keeps its head iced constantly to stay cold.
EISCUE.name: Eiscue

INDEEDEE.blurb: Through its horns, it can pick up on the emotions of creatures around it. Males will act as valets for those they serve.
INDEEDEE.name: Indeedee

MORPEKO.blurb: As it eats the seeds stored up in its pouches, it generates electricity while satisfying its constant hunger.
MORPEKO.name: Morpeko

CUFANT.blurb: If a job requires serious strength, Cufant will excel at it. Its copper body tarnishes in the rain, turning green.
CUFANT.name: Cufant

COPPERAJAH.blurb: These Pokémon live in herds. Their trunks have incredible grip strength, strong enough to crush giant rocks.
COPPERAJAH.name: Copperajah

DRACOZOLT.blurb: The powerful muscles in its tail generate its electricity. Its upper half is entirely too small.
DRACOZOLT.name: Dracozolt

ARCTOZOLT.blurb: The shaking of its freezing upper half is what generates its electricity. It has a hard time walking around.
ARCTOZOLT.name: Arctozolt

DRACOVISH.blurb: Its mighty legs are capable of running at speeds exceeding 40 mph, but it can't breathe unless it's underwater.
DRACOVISH.name: Dracovish

ARCTOVISH.blurb: The skin on its face is impervious to attack, but breathing difficulties made it go extinct anyway.
ARCTOVISH.name: Arctovish

DURALUDON.blurb: Its body resembles polished metal, and it's both lightweight and strong. However, its body rusts easily.
DURALUDON.name: Duraludon

DREEPY.blurb: After being reborn as a ghost, Dreepy wanders the areas it used to inhabit back when it was alive in prehistoric seas.
DREEPY.name: Dreepy

DRAKLOAK.blurb: It's capable of flying faster than 120 mph. It battles alongside Dreepy and dotes on them until they evolve.
DRAKLOAK.name: Drakloak

DRAGAPULT.blurb: Apparently the Dreepy inside its horns eagerly look forward to being launched out at Mach speeds.
DRAGAPULT.name: Dragapult

ZACIAN.blurb: It has slumbered for many years. Some say it is Zamazenta's elder sister, others say the two are rivals.
ZACIAN.name: Zacian

ZAMAZENTA.blurb: It slept for aeons while in the form of a statue. It was asleep for so long, people forgot that it ever existed.
ZAMAZENTA.name: Zamazenta

ETERNATUS.blurb: It was inside a meteorite that fell 20,000 years ago. The energy that its core absorbs allows it to live.
ETERNATUS.name: Eternatus

KUBFU.blurb: If it pulls the long white hair on its head, its fighting spirit heightens and power wells up from deep in its belly.
KUBFU.name: Kubfu

URSHIFU_SINGLE.blurb: Inhabiting the mountains of a distant region, it races across sheer cliffs, training its legs and refining its moves.
URSHIFU_SINGLE.name: Urshifu

ZARUDE.blurb: Once the vines on its body tear off, they become nutrients in the soil. This helps the plants of the forest grow.
ZARUDE.name: Zarude

REGIELEKI.blurb: Its entire body is made of an organ that generates electricity. It is capable of generating a region's worth of electricity.
REGIELEKI.name: Regieleki

REGIDRAGO.blurb: Its body is composed of crystallized dragon energy. It is said to contain the power of every Dragon Pokémon.
REGIDRAGO.name: Regidrago

GLASTRIER.blurb: Glastrier has tremendous physical strength. The mask covering its face is 100 times stronger than diamond.
GLASTRIER.name: Glastrier

SPECTRIER.blurb: As it dashes through the night, it absorbs the life energy of sleeping Pokémon. It craves silence and solitude.
SPECTRIER.name: Spectrier

CALYREX.blurb: Its every move is filled with grace and dignity. Extremely intelligent, it is said to see past, present, and future events.
CALYREX.name: Calyrex

CRAMORANT_GULPING.blurb: The slightest shock is sometimes enough to get this Pokémon to spit out the Arrokuda lodged in its throat.
CRAMORANT_GULPING.name: Cramorant

CRAMORANT_GORGING.blurb: This Cramorant has accidentally gotten a Pikachu lodged in its gullet. While it seems to be choking, it isn't bothered.
CRAMORANT_GORGING.name: Cramorant

TOXTRICITY_LOW_KEY.blurb: While generating electricity, it fills surroundings with what sounds like the strumming of a bass guitar.
TOXTRICITY_LOW_KEY.name: Toxtricity

SINISTEA_CHIPPED.blurb: The swirl pattern in its body is its weakness. If it gets stirred, the swirl loses its shape, and it gets dizzy.
SINISTEA_CHIPPED.name: Sinistea

POLTEAGEIST_CHIPPED.blurb: When angered, it launches tea from its body at the offender's mouth. The tea causes strong chills if swallowed.
POLTEAGEIST_CHIPPED.name: Poltegeist

ALCREMIE_BERRY.blurb: It evolved from a Milcery that held onto a Berry Sweet. The flavor of its cream depends on how it was mixed.
ALCREMIE_BERRY.name: Alcremie

ALCREMIE_LOVE.blurb: It evolved from a Milcery that held onto a Love Sweet. The flavor of its cream depends on how it was mixed.
ALCREMIE_LOVE.name: Alcremie

ALCREMIE_CLOVER.blurb: It evolved from a Milcery that held onto a Clover Sweet. The flavor of its cream depends on how it was mixed.
ALCREMIE_CLOVER.name: Alcremie

ALCREMIE_FLOWER.blurb: It evolved from a Milcery that held onto a Flower Sweet. The flavor of its cream depends on how it was mixed.
ALCREMIE_FLOWER.name: Alcremie

ALCREMIE_RIBBON.blurb: It evolved from a Milcery that held onto a Ribbon Sweet. The flavor of its cream depends on how it was mixed.
ALCREMIE_RIBBON.name: Alcremie

ALCREMIE_STAR.blurb: It evolved from a Milcery that held onto a Star Sweet. The flavor of its cream depends on how it was mixed.
ALCREMIE_STAR.name: Alcremie

EISCUE_NOICE.blurb: The ice covering this Pokémon's face has shattered, revealing a worried expression that many are enamored with.
EISCUE_NOICE.name: Eiscue

INDEEDEE_FEMALE.blurb: These intelligent Pokémon touch horns with each other to share information between them.
INDEEDEE_FEMALE.name: Indeedee

MORPEKO_HANGRY.blurb: Intense hunger drives it to extremes of violence. Until its hunger is appeased, it gets up to all manner of evil deeds.
MORPEKO_HANGRY.name: Morpeko

ZACIAN_CROWNED.blurb: Now armed with a weapon it used in ancient times, this Pokémon needs only a single strike to fell any target.
ZACIAN_CROWNED.name: Zacian

ZAMAZENTA_CROWNED.blurb: Now that it has equipped its shield, it can shrug off impressive blows, even from Dynamaxed foes.
ZAMAZENTA_CROWNED.name: Zamazenta

ETERNATUS_ETERNAMAX.blurb: Infinite amounts of energy pour from this Pokémon's enlarged core, warping the surrounding space-time.
ETERNATUS_ETERNAMAX.name: Eternatus

URSHIFU_RAPID.blurb: This form of Urshifu strongly believes in defeating foes by raining many blows down on them.
URSHIFU_RAPID.name: Urshifu

ZARUDE_DADA.blurb: This Zarude left its pack to raise a human child. It would wrap the child with its cloth to calm the child's crying.
ZARUDE_DADA.name: Zarude

CALYREX_ICE_RIDER.blurb: It is said that this Pokémon once moved a large forest to a new location overnight.

CALYREX_SHADOW_RIDER.blurb: It is said that by using its power, this Pokémon saved the creatures of a forest from a meteorite strike.

MEOWTH_G.blurb: These daring Pokémon have coins on their foreheads. Darker coins are harder, and harder coins garner more respect.
MEOWTH_G.name: Meowth

PONYTA_G.blurb: Its small horn hides a healing power. With a few rubs from this its horn, any slight wound you have will be healed.
PONYTA_G.name: Ponyta

RAPIDASH_G.blurb: Brave and prideful, it dashes airily through the forest, its steps aided by psychic powers stored in its fetlocks.
RAPIDASH_G.name: Rapidash

SLOWPOKE_G.blurb: Because it eats the seeds of a plant that grows only in Galar, their tails have developed a spicy flavor.
SLOWPOKE_G.name: Slowpoke

SLOWBRO_G.blurb: A Shellder bite set off a chemical reaction with the spices inside its body, causing Slowbro to become a Poison-type.
SLOWBRO_G.name: Slowbro

FARFETCHD_G.blurb: It uses the stalks of leeks that are larger and thicker than usual, which made them to adapt to a unique form.
FARFETCHD_G.name: Farfetch'd

WEEZING_G.blurb: This Pokémon consumes particles that contaminate the air. Instead of leaving droppings, it expels clean air.
WEEZING_G.name: Weezing

MR_MIME_G.blurb: It can radiate chilliness from the bottoms of its feet. It'll spend its day tap dancing on a frozen floor.
MR_MIME_G.name: Mr. Mime

ARTICUNO_G.blurb: Known as Articuno, this Pokémon fires beams that can immobilize opponents as if they had been frozen solid.
ARTICUNO_G.name: Articuno

ZAPDOS_G.blurb: One kick from its powerful legs will pulverize a dump truck. It runs through the mountains at over 180 mph.
ZAPDOS_G.name: Zapdos

MOLTRES_G.blurb: Its sinister, flame-like aura consumes the spirit of any creature it hits. Victims become burned-out shadows of themselves.
MOLTRES_G.name: Moltres

SLOWKING_G.blurb: While chanting strange spells, Slowking combines its internal toxins with what it's eaten, creating strange potions.
SLOWKING_G.name: Slowking

CORSOLA_G.blurb: Sudden climate change wiped out this ancient kind of Corsola. It absorbs the life force of others through its branches.
CORSOLA_G.name: Corsola

ZIGZAGOON_G.blurb: It moves in zigzags and wreaks havoc upon its surroundings. It is thought to be the oldest form of Zigzagoon.
ZIGZAGOON_G.name: Zigzagoon

LINOONE_G.blurb: It uses its long tongue to taunt foes. Once the opposition is enraged, it hurls itself, tackling them forcefully.
LINOONE_G.name: Linoone

DARUMAKA_G.blurb: They freeze their breath to make snowballs, using them as ammo for playful snowball fights.
DARUMAKA_G.name: Darumaka

DARMANITAN_G.blurb: Though it has a gentle disposition, it's also very strong. It stashes food in the snowball on its head.
DARMANITAN_G.name: Darmanitan

DARMANITAN_G_ZEN.blurb: Anger has reignited its atrophied flame sac. This Pokémon spews fire all over as it rampages indiscriminately.
DARMANITAN_G_ZEN.name: Darmanitan

YAMASK_G.blurb: It's said that this Pokémon was formed when an ancient clay tablet was drawn to a vengeful spirit.
YAMASK_G.name: Yamask

STUNFISK_G.blurb: Its conspicuous lips lure prey in as it lies in wait in the mud. When prey gets close, it will clamp down hard.
STUNFISK_G.name: Stunfisk

GROWLITHE_H.blurb: These Pokémon live in packs in the snowy mountains and defend themselves with icy breath.
GROWLITHE_H.name: Growlithe

ARCANINE_H.blurb: It is said to guide virtuous people who have lost their way on mountain paths back down to the mountain's base.
ARCANINE_H.name: Arcanine

VOLTORB_H.blurb: When excited, Voltorb discharges the electric current it has stored in its belly, then lets out a great laugh.
VOLTORB_H.name: Voltorb

ELECTRODE_H.blurb: When irritated, this Pokémon lets loose an electric current equal to 20 lightning bolts.
ELECTRODE_H.name: Electrode

TYPHLOSION_H.blurb: It is said to purify lost, forsaken souls with its flames and guide them to the afterlife.
TYPHLOSION_H.name: Typhlosion

QWILFISH_H.blurb: Fisherman detest this troublesome Pokémon because it sprays poison from its spines, getting it everywhere.
QWILFISH_H.name: Qwilfish

SNEASEL_H.blurb: From the tips of its claws drips a venom that infiltrates the nerves of any prey caught in its grasp.
SNEASEL_H.name: Sneasel

SAMUROTT_H.blurb: Hard of heart and deft of blade, its turbulent blows crash into foes like ceaseless pounding waves.
SAMUROTT_H.name: Samurott

LILLIGANT_H.blurb: The leaves on its head are highly valued for medicinal purposes when dried in the sun and boiled.
LILLIGANT_H.name: Lilligant

BASCULIN_H.blurb: This Basculin differs from others in several respects, including its demeanor - this one is gentle.
BASCULIN_H.name: Basculin

ZORUA_H.blurb: A once-departed soul, returned to life. It derives power from resentment, which rises as energy atop its head.
ZORUA_H.name: Zorua

ZOROARK_H.blurb: Heedless of its own safety, it attacks its nemeses with a bitter energy so intense, it lacerates its own body.
ZOROARK_H.name: Zoroark

BRAVIARY_H.blurb: It is said to blast lakes with shock waves, then scoops up any prey that float to the water's surface.
BRAVIARY_H.name: Braviary

SLIGGOO_H.blurb: It is said its metallic shell developed as a result of the mucus on its skin reacting with the iron in ancient water.
SLIGGOO_H.name: Sliggoo

GOODRA_H.blurb: Able to freely control the hardness of its metallic shell. It loathes solitude and is extremely clingy.
GOODRA_H.name: Goodra

AVALUGG_H.blurb: The armor of ice covering its lower jaw puts steel to shame and can shatter rocks with ease.
AVALUGG_H.name: Avalugg

KLEAVOR.blurb: A violent creature that fells towering trees with its crude axes and shields itself with hard stone.
KLEAVOR.name: Kleavor

URSALUNA.blurb: Swampy terrain gave Ursaluna its burly physique and newfound capacity to manipulate peat at will.
URSALUNA.name: Ursaluna
